The Morgan Stanley stock however lost 6.79 percent to 23.07 dollars each at 17:00 GMT.
"This strategic alliance is an important opportunity to accelerate Morgan Stanley's transition to banking holding status," explained Juan Mack, the CEO of the American group.
Morgan Stanley adopted this new statute last week, which would have to allow him to diversify his activities but he makes it happen under the authority of the Federal Reserve.
His alliance with MUFG also confirms that the current financial crisis forces Wall Street's biggest names to adopt far more prudent behavior than before.
The modalities presented last Monday also show that the agreement has been modified over the last few days: last Monday, Morgan had announced that he would sell up to 20% of his shares to Japanese for almost 8.5 billion dollars.
" A week ago, he explained in Tokyo Toshihide Mizuno, the executive director of MUFG, "we thought the participation would have been composed only of ordinary actions.
But in view of the current situation of the economy and the market, we have wanted to minimize risks and cover ourselves. "
On the basis of the weighted average price, MUFG will pay its Morgan Stanley securities by 7 % below its book value.
And the operation will result in a dilution of about 20% of the benefit per action.
The agreement provides that MUFG may convert half of its preferential securities into ordinary shares within one year if they are sold at more than 50 % above the conversion price, or $47 or less, over a given period.
Morgan Stanley assures that the capital provided by MUFG will allow him to take investment opportunities, strengthen his balance sheet and increase his liquidity.
A spokesperson for the group nevertheless refused to elaborate on the strategic projects of the two new allies.
After the investment of MUFG, Morgan Stanley should show a Tier One solvency ratio of about 15%, one of the best in the sector.
Morgan said he had greatly relieved his balance since late August.
The last few weeks were exhausting for the group, which saw its stock exchange price drop by half while the cost of security against a risk of defects on its debt took off.
This cost fell back last Monday but remained at a high level, around 12%.
Last week, Goldman Sachs, the only other "survivor" of Wall Street's big investment banks after the bankruptcies of Bear Stearns and Lehman Brothers and Merrill Lynch's purchase, announced raising $15 billion, partly for Berkshire Hathaway, Warren Buffett's group.
Rafael Correa in Quito, this Monday.
Refound the republic around the socialism of the 21st century.
This is the common project of Venezuelan Hugo Chávez, Bolivian Evo Morales and Ecuadorian Rafael Correa.
This Sunday, following the example of his colleagues and friends, he is the third to put to the vote a draft for a new Constitution.
Mission accomplished since 64% of the voters voted "yes" to the referendum, according to the official results referring to 80% of the votes.
According to these results, the "no" obtained 28%, 7% of the votes were invalid and 0.7% were blank votes.
In order for the draft Constitution to be adopted, it had to obtain half of the votes plus one.
On Sunday, two polls conducted on the way out of the polling stations and a recount by a non-governmental organization had announced a broad "yes" victory, estimating it between 63% and 70%.
Rafael Correa had also claimed the victory of his draft Constitution on Sunday to Monday night.
The "Constitution triumphed overwhelmingly", had assured, congratulating the Ecuadorians who headed the government of Guayaquil, 280 kilometers south-west of Quito.
Thus, Rafael Correa has been congratulated by Chávez and Morales but also by his Chilean colleague Micaela Bachelet.
The elections, which will take place in full calm, according to the observation mission of the Organization of American States (OAS), referred to a text of 444 points that consolidated the " new socialism " defended by the president.
The draft Constitution implies increasing the power of the State over the economy, reserving to it the " development planning " of a country that lives essentially thanks to the extraction of oil by foreign companies and thanks to currencies sent by their emigrants.
Carried by Correa, elected in 2006, the project also grants reinforced powers to the head of State, who can make up to two consecutive terms of four years each and will have the possibility to dissolve the Assembly.
Correa already announced that he would use this power and intend a new mandate in February 2009.
The Constitution further consolidates the principle of free health and education services, which the president began to establish in this country of 13.9 million inhabitants, in which 50% of the population lives below the poverty line.
At last it foresees the interdiction of the presence of foreign troops, which will put an end to the agreement between Quito and Washington for the use of an Ecuadorian base as a starting point for American drug operations.
The 19 abducted persons have been released in Chad
An Egyptian commando launched the assault on the kidnappers of the eleven tourists and their eight companions captured ten days ago.
They're in Cairo.
The eleven European tourists and their eight Egyptian companions kidnapped ten days ago in the desert arrived unharmed in the Egyptian capital after being released on Monday afternoon.
In the morning, they had been released by Egyptian special forces in Chad.
They all looked good on arrival at 15H30 on board a special aircraft to the Al Maza military base adjacent to Cairo International Airport.
Helicopters immediately transported them to Maadi hospital, a residential suburb of Cairo, to undergo medical tests, so they have not been able to speak to the press.
"They are in good health" and "no ransom was paid" to the kidnappers, Egyptian tourism minister Zoheir Garana declared at the airport.
On 19 September, these hostages were held by 35 unknown kidnappers while enjoying a safari on SUVs in a desert area at the foot of Mount Ouanat, in the confines of Egypt, Sudan and Libya, and have since passed from one Zulo to another.
The group consisted of eleven tourists - five Italians, five Germans and one Romanian- and eight Egyptians: two guides, four drivers, a border guard and the director of the travel agency Aegyptous, in charge of the organization of the safari.
An Egyptian security officer indicated that 30 members of the special forces, transported aboard two helicopters, had launched the assault during the night before dawn.
" An exchange of fire occurred, and half of the kidnappers were killed, the others have fled," said this responsible who kept the anonymous.
According to him, 150 members of the Egyptian special forces of the "lightlight" unit were sent to Sudan, where they had the support of German and Italian commandos.
The Italian Foreign Minister, Franco Frattini, mentioned in Belgrade the role played by secret agents and members of the Italian special forces.
"We must recognize that we have achieved this result thanks to the professionalism and effectiveness of our men in the secret services, the special forces," he said without going into details.
He also denied payment of a ransom.
On the eve, the Sudanese army claimed to have intercepted during a patrol an SUV aboard which the kidnappers were present, killing six of them, including the Chadian chief and arresting two of them.
He also stated that they were related to a Darfur rebel group, the Sudan Liberation Movement-Unit (SLA-U), an allegation immediately denied by this group.
